My project is SONAR DETECTION. 
Description of the project- My project includes the prediction of rock or mine present in the sea by submarines. it is very useful for the army espwcially in military wars . The prediction is made by the using given data file sonar data.csv.
Objective

The objective of this project is to predict whether an object detected by sonar signals is a Rock or a Mine using machine learning.

Problem Type

This is a binary classification problem because the output has two possible classes:

M → Mine

R → Rock
I have used logistic regression because 
It is suitable for classification problems.

It works well when the output has two classes.

It is simple and interpretable.

It works effectively for small structured datasets like the Sonar dataset.

Thus, Logistic Regression is an appropriate model for predicting Rock vs Mine.

Dataset Description

Total samples: 208

Total features: 60

Target column: Column 60

 Interpretation & Insights
Key Insights

The sonar dataset can be used to distinguish rocks from mines using signal reflections.

Logistic Regression successfully learns patterns in sonar signals.

The model achieved good accuracy, indicating that the features contain useful information.

The system can be used as a basic mine detection support tool.

